parameters:
Phew...! That was some drinking! It's been a while since
we've had a night like this!

Ah, that's true. Lately, there's been a decree against
wandering at night, but it's just a little breather. If we
drink quickly and head back, there'll be no reprimand!

I wonder how much time has passed since the chancellor
effectively took command of the royal capital.

Lately, Near Lake has been on a path of relentless
territorial expansion. It's quite the honor. They say the
front lines are even equipped with new firearms and magical
weapons that even regular soldiers can use.

As long as you're in the royal capital, your safety is
guaranteed and life keeps getting better. It's hard to
believe when you think about the chaos during the transition
of the throne not too long ago.

I'm really envious of the chancellor. To be favored by that
princess and to have tied the knot with the royal family.
Bloodlines are just for show now, but to think he can do as
he pleases with the princess's beauty every night... it's
unbearable.

While the central district here is mostly peaceful, I don't
hear good things about the order in the lands acquired from
neighboring countries.

The army is more focused on advancing to acquire territory
than on exterminating monster dens. It can't be helped, but
as territory expands, the increase in monsters in
understaffed areas continues.

Maybe that's why there are certain restrictions on going out
after dark. The nights feel much longer than before and it's
somewhat eerie.

Even my hometown in the countryside seems to have started
suffering from monster attacks. The one good thing about the
previous system was that knights managed their own
territories.
Speaking of knights, have you heard this rumor?

There's talk of a wandering knight who appears out of the
darkness on moonlit nights, slays monsters in various
places, and then vanishes back into the night.

I know about it. The mad knight who would cut down anything,
be it monsters, new magical weapons, or enhanced soldiers,
if he found them, right?

The rumor has it that his armor, drenched in blood, is as
black as pitch, and those who see him never live to return.

Ha ha ha! If no one lives to return, then who's spreading
the rumor?!! It's just a tale made up to scare kids and keep
people from wandering at night!
